We recommended and the management agreed to require the Accounting Office to submit to COA the following documents to support the JEV reclassifying the completed projects to the appropriate asset accounts and the transfer of completed projects to the barangays pursuant to Section 5(4) of PD1445, viz:
For the cost of completed projects:
Duly signed Statement of Work Accomplished (SWA);
Agency Inspection Report duly approved by the Local Chief Executive (LCE); and
Certificate of Acceptance by the LGU Oroquieta,  represented by the LCE after a year from the date of completion;
For the transfer of asset/property to the recipient barangay:
MOA entered into by the LGU Oroquieta City and the recipient LGU Brgy;
Certificate of Turn Over and Acceptance by the LGU Oroquieta City and the recipient LGU Barangay; and
JEV drawn by the Barangay Bookkeeper taking up in the recipient barangay’s books of account the cost of the said asset/property received from the city government thus, accountability of the subject asset/property is properly established;
Further, require the Accounting Office to draw a JEV in the General Fund (GF) books of accounts recognizing the receipt of the completed projects which were transferred from TF upon completion, a proof that the said completed projects in the trust fund books were properly accounted for in the agency’s books of accounts, thus, present fairly the PPE accounts in the agency’s financial statements.

